(1)Starting from 1900, Jack spent his life for 98 years;
(2)Starting from 1907, Jack was in elementary school for 6 years;
(3)Jack started junior high in 1913;
(4)Jack graduated from junior high 16 years after the first Nobel Prize was awarded;
(5)Jack was in junior high 94 years less than Jack lived;
(6)Jack started a romantic relationship 14 years after Jack started elementary school;
(7)Jack ended his romantic relationship 19 years after Jack started elementary school;
(8)Jack was in a romantic relationship 1 year less than Jack was in elementary school;
(9)Jack became a father 14 years after World War I started;
(10)Jack joined a company 18 years after World War I started;
(11)Jack retired 87 years after the first Nobel Prize was awarded;
(12)The total duration that Jack worked for a company is 42 years shorter than Jack lived
